      She's a jerk that deserves to be fired if she really meant to use that pedobear on purpose, and I think she did.  The guy served 7 years behind bars.  If they let him out, he should be allowed to start a new life as long as he's not breaking laws.  That woman interfered with that.  I hate pedos, but I also hate drug dealers that sell to kids (or anyone), and I hate thieves, bank robbers, murderers, people who beat people and so on.  It's not ok to destroy his business and call out to the public like that.   If he were a past drug dealer, is it ok to take his ad and put a marijuana leaf, or cocaine bowl on it?  What if he shot someone 10 years back.  Maybe put some artwork to suggest that?  If we warned about every criminal like that there would be dozens of ads that show peoples past offenses.  I guess we could all agree not to accept services from past criminals, but then that would leave less services and a LOT of people out of work. --  There was no reason to put a cartoon bear on a business about computer parts.  She's guilty and deserves punishment. He, however does not.  I would have fired her pronto.  If no one orders computer parts from his store after this, he'd have a case against her.          </div>
